<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC1FFAC23FA8957FE28C252" blockId="19.[151,1074,336,1658]" box="[151,392,336,360]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">DISTRIBUTION (Fig. 7)</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC1FFAC238E8976FCFEC199" blockId="19.[151,1074,336,1658]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
All studies reporting 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D4EFFC1FFAC22AA8976FD05C2B2" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[455,677,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis id="B92DEADFFFC1FFAC22AA8976FD05C2B2" box="[455,677,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Tibicina haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Valais are considered to be incorrect (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC22658989FE0CC29D" author="FUESSLIN, J. C." box="[264,428,399,423]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" refId="ref16256" refString="FUESSLIN, J. C. 1775. Verzeichnis der ihm bekannten Schweitzerischen Inseckten. Bey dem Verfasser und in Commission bey Heinrich Steiner und Compagnie, Zurich und Winterthur, XII + 62 pp." type="book" year="1775">Fuesslin, 1775</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC22D68989FD97C29D" author="STOLL, O." box="[443,567,399,423]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="145 - 208" refId="ref19299" refString="STOLL, O. 1901. Uber xerotherme Relikte in der Schweizer Fauna der Wirbellosen. Jahresberichte der Geographisch-Ethnographischen Gesellschaft in Zurich 2: 145 - 208." type="journal article" year="1901">Stoll, 1901</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC212A8996FD7DC29D" author="KUNTZE, R." box="[583,733,399,423]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="629 - 690" refId="ref17545" refString="KUNTZE, R. 1931. Vergleichende Beobachtungen und Betrachtungen uber die xerotherme Fauna in Podolien, Brandenburg, Osterreich und der Schweiz. Zeitschrift fur Morphologie und Okologie der Tiere 21: 629 - 690." type="journal article" year="1931">Kuntze, 1931</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC21818989FCDDC29D" author="SCHEDL, W." box="[748,893,399,423]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="257 - 271" refId="ref18896" refString="SCHEDL, W. 2000. Taxonomie, Biologie und Verbreitung der Singzikaden Mitteleuropas (Insecta: Homoptera: Cicadidae et Tibicinidae). Berichte des naturwissenschaftlichmedizinischen Vereins Innsbruck 87: 257 - 271." type="journal article" year="2000">Schedl, 2000</bibRefCitation>
) as well as two voucher specimens labelled with “ 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC1FFAC217389A8FDC6C2FC" box="[542,614,430,454]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Wallis</collectingCountry>
” (NMT) and “Martigny” (VS, MNHN). Nevertheless, it is possible that the species could have reached 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC1FFAC205689C8FC1AC2DC" box="[827,954,462,486]" name="Switzerland" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
from three different directions historically,from the north, the south or the west, since it has been published for all neighbouring countries except 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC1FFAC21D78A0BFCEEC11F" box="[698,846,525,549]" name="Liechtenstein" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Liechtenstein</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC1FFAC20338A0BFC2FC11F" box="[862,911,525,549]" name="Italy" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Italy</collectingCountry>
[up to Bozen (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC23F28A2AFE96C17E" author="SCHEDL, W." box="[159,310,556,580]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="231 - 239" refId="ref18931" refString="SCHEDL, W. 2002. Die Verbreitung der funf Singzikaden-Arten in Osterreich (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea). Denisia 04: 231 - 239." type="book chapter" year="2002">Schedl, 2002</bibRefCitation>
) and around Torino (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC21568A2AFD7DC17E" author="GRIFFINI, A." box="[571,733,556,580]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="143 - 144" refId="ref16566" refString="GRIFFINI, A. 1896. Notes sur la faune entomologique piemontaise. X. Cicadidae, Membracidae et Scaridae. Miscellanea Entomologica. Revue Entomologique Internationale 4 (11 - 12): 143 - 144." type="journal article" year="1896">Griffini, 1896</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC219D8A2AFC65C17E" author="DELLA BEFFA, G." box="[752,965,556,580]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="141 - 147" refId="ref15885" refString="DELLA BEFFA, G. 1925. Contributo alla conoscenza della fauna entomologica del Piemonte: Omotteri (Emitteri). Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana 57: 141 - 147." type="journal article" year="1925">Della Beffa, 1925</bibRefCitation>
)], 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC1FFAC20848A2BFB92C17E" box="[1001,1074,557,580]" name="France" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">France</collectingCountry>
[including central parts (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC22B48A4BFDC7C15E" author="HAGEN, H." box="[473,615,588,613]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="340 - 358" refId="ref16703" refString="HAGEN, H. 1855. Die Sing-Cicaden Europa's. Stettiner entomologische Zeitung 16: 340 - 358." type="journal article" year="1855">Hagen, 1855</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC211B8A4AFCBBC15E" author="PUISSANT, S." box="[630,795,588,612]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" refId="ref18488" refString="PUISSANT, S. 2006. Contribution ala connaissance des cigales de France: Geonemie et ecologie des populations (Hemiptera, Cicadidae). Association pour la Caracterisation et l'Etude des Entomocenoses, Bedeilhac et Aynat, 193 pp." type="book" year="2006">Puissant, 2006</bibRefCitation>
)], 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC1FFAC205B8A4AFC25C15E" box="[822,901,588,612]" name="Austria" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Austria</collectingCountry>
[
<collectingRegion id="499DF82FFFC1FFAC20F88A4AFB91C15E" box="[917,1073,588,612]" country="Austria" name="Wien" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Vienna region</collectingRegion>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC23A38A6AFEFAC1B9" author="HAGEN, H." box="[206,346,619,644]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="340 - 358" refId="ref16703" refString="HAGEN, H. 1855. Die Sing-Cicaden Europa's. Stettiner entomologische Zeitung 16: 340 - 358." type="journal article" year="1855">Hagen, 1855</bibRefCitation>
; Wagner &amp;Franz, 1961; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC210E8A6DFD53C1B9" author="SCHEDL, W." box="[611,755,619,643]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="231 - 239" refId="ref18931" refString="SCHEDL, W. 2002. Die Verbreitung der funf Singzikaden-Arten in Osterreich (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea). Denisia 04: 231 - 239." type="book chapter" year="2002">Schedl, 2002</bibRefCitation>
)] and 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC1FFAC205B8A6DFC39C1B9" box="[822,921,619,643]" name="Germany" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Germany</collectingCountry>
[Rhine-Main region (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC22748A8AFE05C199" author="HAGEN, H." box="[281,421,651,676]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="340 - 358" refId="ref16703" refString="HAGEN, H. 1855. Die Sing-Cicaden Europa's. Stettiner entomologische Zeitung 16: 340 - 358." type="journal article" year="1855">Hagen, 1855</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC22DC8A8DFD94C199" author="VOGEL, R." box="[433,564,651,675]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="146 - 154" refId="ref19812" refString="VOGEL, R. 1935. Die blutrote Singzikade (Tibicen haematodes Scop.) in Wurttemberg und Deutschland. Jahreshefte des Vereins fur vaterlandische Naturkunde in Wurttemberg 91: 146 - 154." type="journal article" year="1935">Vogel, 1935</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC212D8A8DFDD8C199" author="VOGEL, R." box="[576,632,651,675]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="116 - 123" refId="ref19846" refString="VOGEL, R. 1937. Weiteres uber Verbreitung und Lebensweise der Blutroten Singzikade (Tibicen haematodes Scop.). Jahreshefte des Vereins fur vaterlandische Naturkunde in Wurttemberg 93: 116 - 123." type="journal article" year="1937">1937</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC21E98A8DFCEBC199" author="SCHWOERBEL, W." box="[644,843,651,675]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="462 - 560" refId="ref19056" refString="SCHWOERBEL, W. 1957. Die Wanzen und Zikaden des Spitzberges bei Tubingen, eine faunistisch-okologische Untersuchung (Hemipteroidea: Heteroptera und Cicadina = Homoptera Auchenorrhyncha). Zeitschrift fur Morphologie und Okologie der Tiere, Berlin 45: 462 - 560." type="journal article" year="1957">Schwoerbel, 1957</bibRefCitation>
)].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC1FFAC238E8AACFEE0C7A0" blockId="19.[151,1074,336,1658]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
With respect to the north, Labram &amp;Imhoff(1845) mentioned 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D4EFFC1FFAC20FB8AACFB8AC1F8" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[918,1066,682,706]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis id="B92DEADFFFC1FFAC20FB8AACFB8AC1F8" box="[918,1066,682,706]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">T.haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as avery rare species in the Basel region. One historic population is mentioned from the vineyards in Rouffach (
<collectingRegion id="499DF82FFFC1FFAC22BB8AEFFD83C03B" box="[470,547,745,769]" country="France" name="Alsace" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Alsace</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC1FFAC21588AEFFDDFC03B" box="[565,639,745,769]" name="France" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">France</collectingCountry>
) situated only 
<quantity id="4CA19B28FFC1FFAC205E8AEFFCDEC03B" box="[819,894,745,769]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" unit="km" value="50.0">50 km</quantity>
north of Basel (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC23F38B0FFEF0C01B" author="DODERLEIN, L." box="[158,336,777,801]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="163 - 174" refId="ref15944" refString="DODERLEIN, L. 1913. Beobachtungen uber elsassische Tiere. Mitteilungen der Philomathischen Gesellschaft in Elsass-Lothringen, Strassbourg 5 (1): 163 - 174." type="journal article" year="1913">Döderlein, 1913</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC22318B0FFE7FC01B" author="HUBER, A." box="[348,479,777,801]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="1 - 120" refId="ref17373" refString="HUBER, A. 1916. Die warmeliebende Tierwelt der weitern Umgebung Basels. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, Berlin, Abteilung A 82 (7): 1 - 120." type="journal article" year="1916">Huber,1916</bibRefCitation>
). 
<specimenCount id="9D5FFD44FFC1FFAC229C8B0FFD21C01B" box="[497,641,777,801]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" type="generic">16 specimens</specimenCount>
of this time are deposited in the collection of the Zoological Museum of Strasbourg labelled with the nearby village of Westhalten (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC22738B4EFE44C05A" author="HUGEL, S. &amp; ATT, F. &amp; ALLOT, H. &amp; ELDTRAUER, J. &amp; RUA, C." box="[286,484,840,864]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="5 - 10" refId="ref17430" refString="HUGEL, S., M ATT, F., C ALLOT, H., F ELDTRAUER, J. &amp; B RUA, C. 2008. Presence de Cicadetta brevipennis Fieber, 1876 en Alsace (Hemiptera, Cicadidae). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de Mulhouse, 64 (1): 5 - 10." type="journal article" year="2008">
Hugel 
<emphasis id="B92DEADFFFC1FFAC22078B4FFE02C05A" box="[362,418,840,864]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">et al.</emphasis>
,2008
</bibRefCitation>
). The German population nearest to 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC1FFAC20148B4EFC58C05A" box="[889,1016,840,864]" name="Switzerland" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
was described from Tübingen (Baden-Württemberg) with apopulation of 80 to 
<specimenCount id="9D5FFD44FFC1FFAC20A08B61FF43C0A4" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" type="generic">100 specimens</specimenCount>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC239E8B80FE1CC0A4" author="SCHWOERBEL, W." box="[243,444,902,926]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="462 - 560" refId="ref19056" refString="SCHWOERBEL, W. 1957. Die Wanzen und Zikaden des Spitzberges bei Tubingen, eine faunistisch-okologische Untersuchung (Hemipteroidea: Heteroptera und Cicadina = Homoptera Auchenorrhyncha). Zeitschrift fur Morphologie und Okologie der Tiere, Berlin 45: 462 - 560." type="journal article" year="1957">Schwoerbel, 1957</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC22BC8B80FDD0C0A4" author="FISCHER, L. H." box="[465,624,902,926]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="237 - 243" refId="ref16236" refString="FISCHER, L. H. 1847. Ueber Sing-Cicaden. Stettiner entomologische Zeitung 8: 237 - 243." type="journal article" year="1847">Fischer (1847)</bibRefCitation>
cited an occurrence from Tuttlingen and Immendingen (Baden-Württemberg) that is only situated 
<quantity id="4CA19B28FFC1FFAC207E8BA0FCFAC084" box="[787,858,934,958]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" unit="km" value="15.0">15 km</quantity>
north of the Swiss border, but had doubts about the identification. To summarize, it is possible that Labram &amp;Imhoff(1845) are correct and 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D4EFFC1FFAC21378BE3FD4FC0C7" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[602,751,997,1021]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis id="B92DEADFFFC1FFAC21378BE3FD4FC0C7" box="[602,751,997,1021]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">T.haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had sporadically occurred in the Basel region, but nevertheless it is more likely that the authors confused it with 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D4EFFC1FFAC23FA8C23FEB9C706" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1772" box="[151,281,1061,1084]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Cicadetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="B92DEADFFFC1FFAC23FA8C23FEB9C706" box="[151,281,1061,1084]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">C. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21E57A4FFC1FFAC224B8C23FEF1C706" box="[294,337,1060,1084]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" sensu="lato">s. l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
A specimen labelled “Winterthur” (ZH) (1900-1910, leg. Huber, NMWI) is considered as doubtful, since it was near ahandwritten label with “cicada from the Mediterranean for comparison”. The location probably refers to the domicile of the collector.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC1FFAC238E8CA4FDF2C600" blockId="19.[151,1074,336,1658]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
With respect to the south, no reliable historic references could be found that 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D4EFFC1FFAC23FA8CC4FE8AC7E0" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[151,298,1218,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis id="B92DEADFFFC1FFAC23FA8CC4FE8AC7E0" box="[151,298,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">T.haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
once occurred in 
<collectingRegion id="499DF82FFFC1FFAC22828CC4FD97C7E0" box="[495,567,1218,1242]" country="Switzerland" name="Ticino" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Ticino</collectingRegion>
. Two unlabelled specimens are deposited in the MCSN collected by Scherrer and Maestri who were active mainly in southern 
<collectingRegion id="499DF82FFFC1FFAC20808CE4FB92C7C0" box="[1005,1074,1250,1274]" country="Switzerland" name="Ticino" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Ticino</collectingRegion>
and especially in the surroundings of Morcote and Melide at the beginning of the 20 
<superScript id="7C2C9B85FFC1FFAC274C8CF9FB92C628" attach="right" box="[1057,1074,1279,1298]" fontSize="8" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">th</superScript>
century (Pollini Paltrinieri, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC1FFAC238E8D44FD54C500" blockId="19.[151,1074,336,1658]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
<materialsCitation id="3B313C90FFC1FFAC238E8D44FD51C500" collectorName="They &amp; Ville &amp; Bernex &amp; Simonet &amp; Schauenberg &amp; Maerky &amp; Wetherefore" country="Switzerland" location="Rhone River" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" specimenCount="2" specimenCount-adult="1" specimenCount-female="1" stateProvince="Geneve">
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC1FFAC238E8D44FE20C660" author="VERNIER, R." box="[227,384,1346,1370]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="147 - 152" refId="ref19779" refString="VERNIER, R. 1996. Un chanteur isole de Lyristes plebejus (Scop.) (Hemiptera, Cicadidae) a l'Allondon. Bulletin romand d'entomologie 14: 147 - 152." type="journal article" year="1996">Vernier (1996)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned ahistorical occurrence of the species for the 
<collectingRegion id="499DF82FFFC1FFAC20B48D44FF7EC640" country="Switzerland" name="Geneve" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Geneva region</collectingRegion>
, the most western part of 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC1FFAC22978D64FDDDC640" box="[506,637,1378,1402]" name="Switzerland" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
. In fact, 
<specimenCount id="9D5FFD44FFC1FFAC21B08D64FC9AC640" box="[733,826,1378,1402]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" type="adult">six adult</specimenCount>
specimens (
<specimenCount id="9D5FFD44FFC1FFAC20A98D64FC4EC640" box="[964,1006,1378,1402]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" type="female">1 ♀</specimenCount>
,5 ♁) and four nymphal skins of 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D4EFFC1FFAC22D58D84FDEBC6A0" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[440,587,1410,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis id="B92DEADFFFC1FFAC22D58D84FDEBC6A0" box="[440,587,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">T.haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingRegion id="499DF82FFFC1FFAC21D18D84FCDFC6A0" box="[700,895,1410,1434]" country="Switzerland" name="Geneve" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Canton of Geneva</collectingRegion>
are preserved in the collection of the MHNG. 
<collectorName id="26AC531BFFC1FFAC22938DA4FD95C680" box="[510,565,1442,1466]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">They</collectorName>
are labelled from the two localities “Pont Butin/Aïre” (western city limit of 
<collectingRegion id="499DF82FFFC1FFAC217B8DC4FDC9C6E0" box="[534,617,1474,1498]" country="Switzerland" name="Geneve" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Geneva</collectingRegion>
) and “Nant de Lagnon” (east of Aire-la- 
<collectorName id="26AC531BFFC1FFAC23FA8DE4FF6DC6C0" box="[151,205,1506,1530]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Ville</collectorName>
, municipality of 
<collectorName id="26AC531BFFC1FFAC22E08DE4FE7CC6C0" box="[397,476,1506,1530]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Bernex</collectorName>
) (leg. 
<collectorName id="26AC531BFFC1FFAC214A8DE4FD23C6C0" box="[551,643,1506,1530]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Simonet</collectorName>
, 
<collectorName id="26AC531BFFC1FFAC21FD8DE4FCBCC6C0" box="[656,796,1506,1530]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Schauenberg</collectorName>
, 
<collectorName id="26AC531BFFC1FFAC20478DE4FCDDC6C0" box="[810,893,1506,1530]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Maerky</collectorName>
or anonymous). 
<collectorName id="26AC531BFFC1FFAC23FA8E04FEBCC520" box="[151,284,1538,1562]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Wetherefore</collectorName>
conclude that areproductive population must have existed along afour kilometre length of the 
<location id="8E866016FFC1FFAC22F98E24FDBCC500" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03F087DBFFC1FFAA23FA88E5FC02C189:8E866016FFC1FFAC22F98E24FDBCC500" box="[404,540,1570,1594]" country="Switzerland" name="Rhone River" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" stateProvince="Geneve">Rhone River</location>
from 1914 to 1947
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC1FFAC238E8E44FB91C540" blockId="19.[151,1074,336,1658]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
<materialsCitation id="3B313C90FFC1FFAC238E8E44FB91C540" location="Rhone River" municipality="Basel region" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Ticino">
Despite recent intense field work, 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D4EFFC1FFAC213F8E44FD45C560" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[594,741,1602,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis id="B92DEADFFFC1FFAC213F8E44FD45C560" box="[594,741,1602,1626]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">T.haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found neither in southern 
<collectingRegion id="499DF82FFFC1FFAC23FA8E64FF7CC540" box="[151,220,1634,1658]" country="Switzerland" name="Ticino" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Ticino</collectingRegion>
nor in the 
<collectingMunicipality id="6B82ACB7FFC1FFAC220F8E64FE50C540" box="[354,496,1634,1658]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Basel region</collectingMunicipality>
. When investigating the slopes of the 
<location id="8E866016FFC1FFAC20C88E64FB91C540" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03F087DBFFC1FFAA23FA88E5FC02C189:8E866016FFC1FFAC20C88E64FB91C540" box="[933,1073,1634,1658]" municipality="Basel region" name="Rhone River" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" stateProvince="Ticino">Rhone River</location>
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC6FFAB21548D19FDCCC60E" blockId="20.[136,1059,1311,1388]" box="[569,620,1311,1332]" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">FIG.7</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC6FFAB23E58D3BFE9CC656" blockId="20.[136,1059,1311,1388]" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">
Distribution map of 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D4EFFC6FFAB220D8D3BFD8FC669" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[352,559,1341,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis id="B92DEADFFFC6FFAB220D8D3BFD8FC669" box="[352,559,1341,1363]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">Tibicina haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(top) including the data source for the records presented (below).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC6FFAB23E58D8AFB80C53E" blockId="20.[136,1059,1420,1541]" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">
downstream of 
<collectingRegion id="499DF82FFFC6FFAB225C8D8AFE22C69E" box="[305,386,1420,1444]" country="Switzerland" name="Geneve" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">Geneva</collectingRegion>
two small populations of 3to 4singing males each were discovered at the historically known localities Pont Butin and Nant de Lagnon in 2012 and asingle singing specimen was discovered at Cartigny (GE) in 2011and in 2012. These are the first known observations of the species for more than 60 years in 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC6FFAB20F78DEAFBBDC53E" box="[922,1053,1516,1540]" name="Switzerland" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3436546FFC6FFAA23E58E24FC02C189" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="250" pageId="20" pageNumber="249" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC6FFAB23E58E24FEDBC502" blockId="20.[136,1059,1570,1657]" box="[136,379,1570,1593]" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">ECOLOGY AND THREAT</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC6FFAB23B98E47FB82C543" blockId="20.[136,1059,1570,1657]" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">
<materialsCitation id="3B313C90FFC6FFAB23B98E47FB82C543" county="The" location="At" municipality="Swiss" pageId="20" pageNumber="249" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Geneve">
<collectingCounty id="62874E41FFC6FFAB23B98E47FF5DC563" box="[212,253,1601,1625]" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">The</collectingCounty>
historic and recent 
<collectingMunicipality id="6B82ACB7FFC6FFAB22BD8E47FDAEC563" box="[464,526,1601,1625]" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">Swiss</collectingMunicipality>
habitats in the 
<collectingRegion id="499DF82FFFC6FFAB21DC8E47FCF6C563" box="[689,854,1601,1625]" country="Switzerland" name="Geneve" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">Geneva Region</collectingRegion>
are oak dominated deciduous woodland on steep slopes. 
<location id="8E866016FFC6FFAB217A8E67FD92C543" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03F087DBFFC1FFAA23FA88E5FC02C189:8E866016FFC6FFAB217A8E67FD92C543" box="[535,562,1633,1657]" county="The" municipality="Swiss" name="At" pageId="20" pageNumber="249" stateProvince="Geneve">At</location>
the 
<location id="8E866016FFC6FFAB210D8E67FD72C543" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03F087DBFFC1FFAA23FA88E5FC02C189:8E866016FFC6FFAB210D8E67FD72C543" box="[608,722,1633,1657]" county="The" municipality="Swiss" name="Pont Butin" pageId="20" pageNumber="249" stateProvince="Geneve">Pont Butin</location>
locality 
<specimenCount id="9D5FFD44FFC6FFAB205D8E67FC6DC543" box="[816,973,1633,1657]" pageId="20" pageNumber="249" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
entered
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC7FFAA23FA88E2FD60C263" blockId="21.[151,1074,227,691]" pageId="21" pageNumber="250">
a small orchard in 2012. An occurrence in vineyards is not documented for 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC7FFAA23FA8904FEBAC220" box="[151,282,258,282]" name="Switzerland" pageId="21" pageNumber="250">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
. The site Pont Butin/Aïre seems to be adversely affected by settlements. The Rouffach population (
<collectingRegion id="499DF82FFFC7FFAA22D58924FDA5C200" box="[440,517,290,314]" country="France" name="Alsace" pageId="21" pageNumber="250">Alsace</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC7FFAA217F8924FDFCC200" box="[530,604,290,314]" name="France" pageId="21" pageNumber="250">France</collectingCountry>
) was endangered through the collecting of this attractive species by dealers (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC7FFAA216D8947FD13C263" author="DODERLEIN, L." box="[512,691,321,345]" pageId="21" pageNumber="250" pagination="163 - 174" refId="ref15944" refString="DODERLEIN, L. 1913. Beobachtungen uber elsassische Tiere. Mitteilungen der Philomathischen Gesellschaft in Elsass-Lothringen, Strassbourg 5 (1): 163 - 174." type="journal article" year="1913">Döderlein, 1913</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC7FFAA238E8967FB85C16F" blockId="21.[151,1074,227,691]" pageId="21" pageNumber="250">
<taxonomicName id="4C594D4EFFC7FFAA238E8967FE63C243" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[227,451,353,377]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis id="B92DEADFFFC7FFAA238E8967FE63C243" box="[227,451,353,377]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="250">Tibicina haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an indigenous, but extremely rare Swiss species. The current population size is about 10 calling males. It is interesting that we have found the species 60 years after the last record at exactly the same localities. Either the two small but striking populations have been continuously present without any public recognition or the species has re-immigrated to its former habitats. The population in the Val des Usses (Haute-Savoie, 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC7FFAA216E89F8FDEDC12C" box="[515,589,510,534]" name="France" pageId="21" pageNumber="250">France</collectingCountry>
) mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B3CFFC7FFAA219A89F8FC34C12C" author="VERNIER, R." box="[759,916,510,534]" pageId="21" pageNumber="250" pagination="147 - 152" refId="ref19779" refString="VERNIER, R. 1996. Un chanteur isole de Lyristes plebejus (Scop.) (Hemiptera, Cicadidae) a l'Allondon. Bulletin romand d'entomologie 14: 147 - 152." type="journal article" year="1996">Vernier (1996)</bibRefCitation>
is still present according to regular observations until 2010 (Bal, pers. comm.). Given its short distance of only 
<quantity id="4CA19B28FFC7FFAA22408A3BFED2C16F" box="[301,370,573,597]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="250" unit="km" value="15.0">15 km</quantity>
from the Swiss border,it might serve as apool for immigration.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636CDFFC7FFAA23FA8A5AFC02C189" blockId="21.[151,1074,227,691]" pageId="21" pageNumber="250">
With the rise of more ecologically sensitive approaches to viticulture, supported by a milder climate, 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D4EFFC7FFAA22208A7BFE46C1AE" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[333,486,636,660]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haematodes">
<emphasis id="B92DEADFFFC7FFAA22208A7BFE46C1AE" box="[333,486,636,660]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="250">T. haematodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be establish more numerous populations in 
<collectingCountry id="F34E765DFFC7FFAA23FA8A9DFEBAC189" box="[151,282,667,691]" name="Switzerland" pageId="21" pageNumber="250">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
. Nevertheless, the species is currently critically endangered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
